  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.7,
      "text": "This is the Libervax recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.64,
      "end": 12.22,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit Libervax.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.26,
      "end": 19.22,
      "text": "Recorded by Annie Coleman in St. Louis, Missouri in January 2006.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 20.88,
      "end": 24.72,
      "text": "Asaps Fables, the milkmaid and her pale.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 26.54,
      "end": 31.2,
      "text": "A farmer's daughter had been out to milk the cows and was returning to the dairy,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 31.54,
      "end": 33.62,
      "text": "carrying her pale of milk upon her head.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 34.36,
      "end": 38.38,
      "text": "As she walked along, she fell, amusing after this fashion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 39.16,
      "end": 45.28,
      "text": "The milk in this pale will provide me with cream, which I will make into butter and take to market to sell.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 46.0,
      "end": 51.8,
      "text": "With the money, I will buy a number of eggs, and these, when hatched, will produce chickens,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 52.42,
      "end": 56.66,
      "text": "and bind by, I shall have quite a large poultry-yard.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 57.5,
      "end": 62.52,
      "text": "Then I shall sell some of my fowls, and with the money which they will bring in,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 63.04,
      "end": 67.4,
      "text": "I will buy myself a new gown, which I shall wear when I go to the fair,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 68.1,
      "end": 72.9,
      "text": "and all the young fellows will admire it, and come and make love to me.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 73.46,
      "end": 76.74,
      "text": "But I shall toss my head and have nothing to say to them.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 77.6,
      "end": 83.04,
      "text": "Forgetting all about the pale and suiting the action to the word, she tossed her head.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 83.92,
      "end": 91.54,
      "text": "Down went the pale, all the milk was spilled, and all her fine castles in the air vanished in a moment.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 92.56,
      "end": 96.0,
      "text": "Do not count your chickens before they are hatched.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 97.68,
      "end": 99.82,
      "text": "End of the milkmaid and her pale.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
